{{infobox Museum |name= Buduruwagala Archaeological Museum |image=Buduruwagala Museum 2.jpg |caption =Archaeological Museum, Buduruwagala |coordinates = |established= 1988<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.srisalike.com/Museum/Monaragala/buduruwagala%20Museum.aspx | title=Buduruwagala Museum | publisher=srisalike.com | accessdate=22 June 2015}}</ref> |founder = |location= [[Buduruwagala]], [[Sri Lanka]] |director= |visitors = |type = Archaeological |website= http://www.archaeology.gov.lk }}
'''Buduruwagala Archaeological Museum''' is a regional museum located in [[Buduruwagala]], [[Sri Lanka]]. It was founded in 1988 and owned by [[Department of Archaeology (Sri Lanka)|Department of Archaeology of Sri Lanka]].
The museum is used to show archaeological objects found in Buduruwagala area and also exhibits relics belonging to [[Anuradhapura]], [[Polonnaruwa]] and [[Kandy]] periods.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.archaeology.gov.lk/web/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=78&Itemid=86&lang=en | title=Buduruwagala Museum (Regional) | publisher=archaeology.gov.lk | accessdate=22 June 2015}}</ref>
==Opening hours== The museum is open from 8.30 AM to 5.00 PM and close on Tuesday.
