'''Gabriel Adrien Robinet de Cléry''' (18 August 1836 - 1914) was a French magistrate, historian and legal writer active during the [[Second French Empire]] and the [[Third French Republic]]. He was a convinced [[Legitimists|Legitimist]]. He was born in [[Metz]] and died in [[Paris]].

