'''Dr. Robert Anthony Beddard''' was, until 2006, the Cowen [[Fellow]] and [[Tutor]] in [[History|Modern History]], [[Oriel College, Oxford]].<ref>https://archive.is/20120630225029/http://www.btinternet.com/~akme/ocloril2.html</ref> He holds a master's degree ([[Master of Arts|MA]]), a Doctorate ([[Doctor of Philosophy]]), a [[University of Cambridge|Cambridge]] [[Master of Arts (Oxbridge and Dublin)|Master's]] (MA) and a Bachelor's ([[Bachelor of Arts|BA]]) from [[University of London|London]]. He was a fellow [[Queens' College, Cambridge]] from 1965 to 1968.<ref>http://www.quns.cam.ac.uk/page-249</ref> He is a [[Royal Historical Society|Fellow of the Royal Historical Society]].<ref>https://books.google.com/books?id=k_3CETsokjEC&pg=PA231&lpg=PA231&dq=Robert+Beddard+Cowen+Fellow&source=bl&ots=cBdvCvMNsi&sig=UK7dI4D5IlfGnjTPoTWvgOZcrss&hl=en&ei=YUKiS_-qMY61tgensKmjCg&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=10&ved=0CBwQ6AEwCQ#v=onepage&q=Robert%20Beddard%20Cowen%20Fellow&f=false</ref> His research interests lie in 17th century [[British politics]] and [[religion]], and include relations between [[House of Stuart|Stuart England]] and [[Rome]].<ref>http://www.history.ox.ac.uk/staff/faculty/beddard_rapj.htm</ref>
