{{italic title}}
'''''Vita Ansgari''''' is the biography of [[Ansgar]], written by [[Rimbert]], his successor as archbishop in [[Hamburg-Bremen]]. Written in about 875 CE, the ''Vita'' is an important source in not only detailing Ansgar's missionary work in Scandinavia but in its descriptions of the everyday lives of people during the [[Viking Age]].<ref>{{Cite book |last=Jesch |first=Judith |authorlink= |title=Women in the Viking Age |publisher=Boydell Press |year=1991 |location= |pages=89 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=9xpNRpI9zFoC&printsec=frontcover#v=onepage&q=&f=false |doi=  |isbn=978-0-85115-360-5}}</ref>

